FBIS3-33434 "drlat037_b_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 Haiti Potential Closure of Radio Lumiere Due to High Oil Prices FL2302221494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 GMT 22 Feb 94 FL2302221494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio Language: French Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] A cessation of activities is imminent at Radio Lumiere. The very high cost of oil products has prompted the officials of Radio Lumiere to consider ceasing all activities within two weeks. On 22 February, officials of the Protestant radio station commemorated its 35th anniversary by calling on evangelical Christians to make financial contributions so the radio station can continue its broadcasts. Raymond Exume, general manager of the satellite stations of Radio Lumiere, says he considers a shutdown of Radio Lumiere a failure that will have consequences for the entire Haitian evangelical community. [passage omitted]
